Yes, that's an easy fix! The issue is that the resetQuizzesExpanded() function is resetting the radio buttons and clearing the score display, but it's not clearing the individual question feedback messages.

Here's the updated resetQuizzesExpanded() function that will clear both the selections AND the feedback messages:

```javascript
function resetQuizzesExpanded() {
    // Reset all radio button selections
    document.querySelectorAll('.quiz-question input').forEach(i => i.checked = false);
    
    // Clear all feedback messages and hide them
    document.querySelectorAll('.quiz-feedback').forEach(f => { 
        f.style.display = 'none'; 
        f.innerHTML = ''; 
        // Also remove any styling classes
        f.classList.remove('feedback-correct', 'feedback-incorrect');
    });
    
    // Clear the overall score display
    document.getElementById('quizScore').innerHTML = '';
}
```

Just replace your existing resetQuizzesExpanded() function with this updated version. It does three things:

1. Clears radio selections (same as before)
2. Clears each question's feedback - removes the text content and hides the feedback div
3. Clears the overall score display (same as before)

Now when you click "Reset All", it will completely clear both the selected answers AND any feedback comments (like "Correct!" or "Incorrect. Review the material.") from each question.
